<h1>LDD Sets</h1>
<p>Because I am completely crazy, I’ve taken the time to convert various LEGO sets (just ones from LEGO Education so far) to
	<a href="http://ldd.lego.com/">LEGO Digital Designer</a>, so you can build things from the set of your choice without physically having it. This is also
	convenient if you have the set and you wish to LDD a thing you have already built, since you don’t have to go hunting around for the right part. Here are all
	the sets I’ve done so far:
</p>
<p><strong>EV3 Core Set (45544)</strong></p>
<p><a href="/img/EV3_Core_45544.png"><img id="Set" src="/img/EV3_Core_45544.png"></a></p>
<p><a href="/img/EV3_Core_45544.lxf">Download EV3_Core_45544.lxf</a></p>
